/// Dynamic row-level security — maps the signed-in user (USERPRINCIPALNAME) to the
/// banners they're allowed to see via a security bridge table `dim_user_banner`
/// (user_email, banner_id). Add that table in a later iteration; the pattern is the
/// production-grade approach (one role, data-driven) vs a role per banner.
role 'RLS Dynamic Banner by UPN'
	modelPermission: read

	tablePermission dim_store =
			VAR _user = USERPRINCIPALNAME()
			VAR _allowed =
			    CALCULATETABLE(
			        VALUES(dim_user_banner[banner_id]),
			        dim_user_banner[user_email] = _user
			    )
			RETURN
			    dim_store[banner_id] IN _allowed

